[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    232[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mConflict: Security Finding 4 (TCPA over-compliance) vs. recipe author's likely defensive posture.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The recipe is stricter than the regulatory floor on TCPA. A security reviewer who represents "don't get sued" will argue for keeping the strict posture. A security reviewer who represents "accurate regulatory picture for the reader" will argue for nuance. Resolution: the cookbook's pedagogical mission favors accurate nuance over defensive maximalism. Readers building production systems will make their own risk-based choices; the cookbook's job is to describe the actual floor. Recommend rewriting the prerequisites row to acknowledge the healthcare exemption while noting that many orgs choose to exceed it.[K
