[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    309[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m##[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mThe AWS Implementation[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    310[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    311[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhy These Services[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    312[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    313[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon S3 for the cross-facility data lake.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Three zones: raw (every inbound query payload, every outbound query response, every linkage-submission CCD or FHIR Bundle, exactly as received, partitioned by participating-organization and date for audit and replay), curated (parsed match decisions and release decisions with full provenance), and derived (cohort-stratified match-quality reports, per-organization match-quality scorecards, consent-coverage analytics). S3 is HIPAA-eligible under BAA with SSE-KMS encryption. The raw payloads are retained for the regulatory retention floor; the curated decisions power both the operational layer and the analytics layer.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    314[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    315[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon DynamoDB for the cross-org MPI and the audit-log primary store.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Two tables: a cross-org MPI table keyed on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m(local_patient_id)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m with attributes for the cross-organizational identifier, the participating-organization links, the demographic snapshot at last match, the match-confidence-history; and an audit-log table keyed on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m(query_id, event_seq)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m with the full lifecycle of each query (inbound, normalized, evaluated, consent-checked, released-or-withheld, completed). DynamoDB's single-digit-millisecond reads support the latency budget for query-time match. Streams from both tables feed downstream consumers (longitudinal-record-assembler, audit-log replicator).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    316[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    317[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon ElastiCache (Redis) for the blocking-index and consent-state cache.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Blocking indices are read on every query and are amenable to caching. The blocking-key-to-candidate-set map is loaded from DynamoDB at warm-up and refreshed incrementally as the MPI changes; the cache holds the most-frequently-queried blocks. Consent state is also read on every query, but consent reads must fall through to the system-of-record on miss (caching consent risks releasing data after revocation). Both caches use TLS in-transit and KMS at-rest encryption. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO: confirm ElastiCache HIPAA eligibility and the encryption-at-rest configuration at time of build. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    318[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    319[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SQS for the query queues.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Three queues: a high-priority queue for synchronous query-time matching (with a short visibility timeout and a strict latency budget), a standard queue for asynchronous linkage-submission processing (each new CCD or FHIR Bundle gets matched against the MPI to determine whether it is a new identity or an existing one), and a deferred-review queue for cases where the matcher's confidence falls in the review band. Separating the queues prevents linkage-submission load from delaying query-time matching.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    320[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    321[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Lambda for the per-query and per-submission processing.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Lambda is the right substrate because each query is short-lived, mostly I/O-bound (DynamoDB reads plus the matcher computation), and benefits from on-demand scaling for the bursty pattern of clinical-workflow queries. Separate Lambdas per pipeline stage: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mnormalize-query[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevaluate-match[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mapply-consent-and-sensitivity[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrelease-and-audit[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprocess-linkage-submission[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m. Each is in VPC with VPC endpoints for downstream services. Outbound queries to participating organizations or to HIE intermediaries go through NAT Gateway with an allow-list of known endpoints, with PrivateLink where the partner offers it. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO: confirm partner PrivateLink availability at time of build; HIE intermediaries vary in their connectivity options. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    322[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    323[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway plus Lambda for the inbound query endpoint.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Other organizations and HIE intermediaries call the API to query for patients. API Gateway provides authentication via mutual TLS (the HIE participation agreement specifies certificate-based identity for queriers), request logging, request signing verification, and rate limiting per requester. The endpoint exposes both PIX/PDQ (for legacy v2 queries) and FHIR Patient [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m$match[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m (for FHIR-native queries) with shared backend logic.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    324[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    325[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Step Functions for orchestration.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Three workflows: a query-time-match workflow (normalize, evaluate, consent-check, release-and-audit, with strict latency budgets and timeouts at each stage), a linkage-submission workflow (parse the inbound CCD or FHIR Bundle, normalize, evaluate against the MPI, persist the match decision, propagate to downstream consumers), and an MPI-reconciliation workflow (run periodically to compare the local MPI to the participating-organizations' aggregated demographic snapshots and detect drift).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    326[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon EventBridge for cross-facility events and downstream propagation.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m When a query is resolved ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcross_facility_query_resolved[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m), when a linkage submission produces a new or updated cross-org identifier ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcross_facility_identifier_resolved[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m), when a consent change invalidates prior matches ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcross_facility_match_invalidated[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m), an event flows out to downstream consumers: the longitudinal-record-assembler, the patient-portal access-report generator, the consent-management workflow, the local patient matcher (5.1, when the cross-facility match surfaces a previously-unknown internal duplicate signal), the longitudinal name-change matcher (5.7), and the privacy-preserving linkage layer (5.8) where applicable. EventBridge rules route events to the right consumer, with DLQs configured for failed deliveries.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    328[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
